.TH "ib_umem_odp_alloc_child" 9 "ib_umem_odp_alloc_child" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_umem_odp_alloc_child \- Allocate a child ODP umem under an implicit parent ODP umem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_umem_odp *" ib_umem_odp_alloc_child
.BI "(struct ib_umem_odp *root "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "const struct mmu_interval_notifier_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "root" 12
The parent umem enclosing the child. This must be allocated using
\fBib_alloc_implicit_odp_umem\fP
.IP "addr" 12
The starting userspace VA
.IP "size" 12
The length of the userspace VA
.IP "ops" 12
MMU interval ops, currently only \fIinvalidate\fP
